34Status GetAxisForPackAndUnpack(InferenceContext* c, int32 rank_after_pack,
35 int32* axis) {
36 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->GetAttr("axis", axis));
37 if (*axis < -1 * rank_after_pack || *axis >= rank_after_pack) {
38 return errors::InvalidArgument("Invalid axis: ", *axis, "; must be in [",
39 -1 * rank_after_pack, ",", rank_after_pack,
40 ")");
41 }
42 if (*axis < 0) *axis = (rank_after_pack + *axis);
43 return Status::OK();
44}
45
46template <typename T>
47std::vector<int64> AsInt64(const Tensor* tensor, int64 num_elements) {
48 std::vector<int64> ret(num_elements);
49 auto data = tensor->vec<T>();
50 for (int64 i = 0; i < num_elements; ++i) {
51 ret[i] = data(i);
52 }
53 return ret;
54}
55
56template <typename T>
57Status PadKnown(InferenceContext* c, ShapeHandle input,
58 const Tensor* paddings_t, int64 num_dims) {
59 // paddings_t is known.
60 std::vector<DimensionHandle> dims(num_dims);
61 auto paddings_data = paddings_t->matrix<T>();
62 for (int64 i = 0; i < num_dims; ++i) {
63 const T pad0 = paddings_data(i, 0);
64 const T pad1 = paddings_data(i, 1);
65 if (pad0 < 0 || pad1 < 0) {
66 return errors::InvalidArgument("Paddings must be non-negative");
67 }
68 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Add(c->Dim(input, i), pad0 + pad1, &dims[i]));
69 }
70 c->set_output(0, c->MakeShape(dims));
71 return Status::OK();
72}
73
74Status PadShapeFn(InferenceContext* c) {
75 // Paddings is a matrix of [input_rank, 2].
76 ShapeHandle paddings;
77 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(c->input(1), 2, &paddings));
78 DimensionHandle unused;
79 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithValue(c->Dim(paddings, 1), 2, &unused));
80
81 // n_dim and input.rank are equivalent.
82 ShapeHandle input = c->input(0);
83 DimensionHandle n_dim = c->Dim(paddings, 0);
84 if (c->ValueKnown(n_dim)) {
85 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(input, c->Value(n_dim), &input));
86 } else if (c->RankKnown(input)) {
87 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithValue(n_dim, c->Rank(input), &n_dim));
88 }
89
90 const Tensor* paddings_t = c->input_tensor(1);
91
92 // paddings_t is unknown
93 if (paddings_t == nullptr) {
94 if (c->ValueKnown(n_dim)) {
95 // Make output with n_dim unknown dims.
96 c->set_output(0, c->UnknownShapeOfRank(c->Value(n_dim)));
97 } else {
98 c->set_output(0, c->UnknownShape());
99 }
100 return Status::OK();
101 }
102
103 const int64 num_dims = paddings_t->shape().dim_size(0);
104 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(input, num_dims, &input));
105 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithValue(n_dim, num_dims, &n_dim));
106
107 if (paddings_t->dtype() == DT_INT32) {
108 return PadKnown<int32>(c, input, paddings_t, num_dims);
109 } else {
110 return PadKnown<int64>(c, input, paddings_t, num_dims);
111 }
112}
113
114Status TransposeShapeFn(InferenceContext* c) {
115 ShapeHandle input = c->input(0);
116 ShapeHandle perm_shape = c->input(1);
117 const Tensor* perm = c->input_tensor(1);
118 DimensionHandle perm_elems = c->NumElements(perm_shape);
119 // If we don't have rank information on the input or value information on
120 // perm we can't return any shape information, otherwise we have enough
121 // information to at least find the rank of the output.
122 if (!c->RankKnown(input) && !c->ValueKnown(perm_elems) && perm == nullptr) {
123 c->set_output(0, c->UnknownShape());
124 return Status::OK();
125 }
126
127 // Find our value of the rank.
128 int64 rank;
129 if (c->RankKnown(input)) {
130 rank = c->Rank(input);
131 } else if (c->ValueKnown(perm_elems)) {
132 rank = c->Value(perm_elems);
133 } else {
134 rank = perm->NumElements();
135 }
136 std::vector<DimensionHandle> dims;
137 dims.resize(rank);
138 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(input, rank, &input));
139 // Ensure that perm is a vector and has rank elements.
140 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(perm_shape, 1, &perm_shape));
141 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithValue(perm_elems, rank, &perm_elems));
142
143 // If we know the rank of the input and the value of perm, we can return
144 // all shape informantion, otherwise we can only return rank information,
145 // but no information for the dimensions.
146 if (perm != nullptr) {
147 std::vector<int64> data;
148 if (perm->dtype() == DT_INT32) {
149 data = AsInt64<int32>(perm, rank);
150 } else {
151 data = AsInt64<int64>(perm, rank);
152 }
153
154 for (int32 i = 0; i < rank; ++i) {
155 int64 in_idx = data[i];
156 if (in_idx >= rank) {
157 return errors::InvalidArgument("perm dim ", in_idx,
158 " is out of range of input rank ", rank);
159 }
160 dims[i] = c->Dim(input, in_idx);
161 }
162 } else {
163 for (int i = 0; i < rank; ++i) {
164 dims[i] = c->UnknownDim();
165 }
166 }
167
168 c->set_output(0, c->MakeShape(dims));
169 return Status::OK();
170}
171
172Status SetOutputShapeForReshape(InferenceContext* c) {
173 ShapeHandle in = c->input(0);
174 ShapeHandle out;
175 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->MakeShapeFromShapeTensor(1, &out));
176
177 if (!c->RankKnown(out)) {
178 // We have no information about the shape of the output.
179 c->set_output(0, out);
180 return Status::OK();
181 }
182
183 if (c->RankKnown(out) && c->RankKnown(in)) {
184 // We don't know the number of output elements, but we can try to infer
185 // the missing dimension.
186 bool too_many_unknown = false;
187 int32 out_unknown_idx = -1;
188
189 DimensionHandle known_out_elems = c->NumElements(out);
190 if (!c->ValueKnown(known_out_elems)) {
191 known_out_elems = c->MakeDim(1);
192 for (int32 i = 0; i < c->Rank(out); ++i) {
193 DimensionHandle dim = c->Dim(out, i);
194 if (!c->ValueKnown(dim)) {
195 if (out_unknown_idx >= 0) {
196 too_many_unknown = true;
197 break;
198 }
199 out_unknown_idx = i;
200 } else {
201 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
202 c->Multiply(known_out_elems, dim, &known_out_elems));
203 }
204 }
205 }
206 int32 in_unknown_idx = -1;
207 DimensionHandle known_in_elems = c->NumElements(in);
208 if (!c->ValueKnown(known_in_elems)) {
209 known_in_elems = c->MakeDim(1);
210 for (int32 i = 0; i < c->Rank(in); ++i) {
211 DimensionHandle dim = c->Dim(in, i);
212 if (!c->ValueKnown(dim)) {
213 if (in_unknown_idx >= 0) {
214 too_many_unknown = true;
215 break;
216 }
217 in_unknown_idx = i;
218 } else {
219 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Multiply(known_in_elems, dim, &known_in_elems));
220 }
221 }
222 }
223
224 if (!too_many_unknown) {
225 if (in_unknown_idx < 0 && out_unknown_idx < 0) {
226 // Just check that the dimensions match.
227 if (c->Value(known_in_elems) != c->Value(known_out_elems)) {
228 return errors::InvalidArgument(
229 "Cannot reshape a tensor with ", c->DebugString(known_in_elems),
230 " elements to shape ", c->DebugString(out), " (",
231 c->DebugString(known_out_elems), " elements)");
232 }
233 } else if (in_unknown_idx < 0 && out_unknown_idx >= 0 &&
234 c->Value(known_out_elems) > 0) {
235 // Input fully known, infer the one missing output dim
236 DimensionHandle inferred_dim;
237 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Divide(known_in_elems, c->Value(known_out_elems),
238 true /* evenly_divisible */,
239 &inferred_dim));
240 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
241 c->ReplaceDim(out, out_unknown_idx, inferred_dim, &out));
242
243 } else if (in_unknown_idx >= 0 && out_unknown_idx < 0 &&
244 c->Value(known_in_elems) != 0) {
245 // Output fully known, infer the one missing input dim
246 DimensionHandle inferred_dim;
247 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Divide(known_out_elems, c->Value(known_in_elems),
248 true /* evenly_divisible */,
249 &inferred_dim));
250 DimensionHandle unknown_in_dim = c->Dim(in, in_unknown_idx);
251 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
252 c->Merge(unknown_in_dim, inferred_dim, &unknown_in_dim));
253 } else if (in_unknown_idx >= 0 && out_unknown_idx >= 0) {
254 // Exactly one unknown dimension in both input and output. These 2 are
255 // equal iff the known elements are equal.
256 if (c->Value(known_in_elems) == c->Value(known_out_elems)) {
257 DimensionHandle unknown_in_dim = c->Dim(in, in_unknown_idx);
258 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
259 c->ReplaceDim(out, out_unknown_idx, unknown_in_dim, &out));
260 }
261 }
262 }
263 }
264 c->set_output(0, out);
265 return Status::OK();
266}

270REGISTER_OP("ParallelConcat")
271 .Input("values: N * T")
272 .Output("output: T")
273 .Attr("N: int >= 1")
274 .Attr("T: type")
275 .Attr("shape: shape")
276 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
277 // Validate that the shape attr is correct.
278 PartialTensorShape shape;
279 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->GetAttr("shape", &shape));
280 ShapeHandle passed_shape;
281 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
282 c->MakeShapeFromPartialTensorShape(shape, &passed_shape));
283 if (!c->FullyDefined(passed_shape)) {
284 return errors::InvalidArgument("shape attr must be fully defined.");
285 }
286 ShapeHandle cur;
287 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->ReplaceDim(
288 passed_shape, 0, c->MakeDim(shape_inference::DimensionOrConstant(1)),
289 &cur));
290 for (int i = 0; i < c->num_inputs(); ++i) {
291 if (!c->FullyDefined(c->input(i))) {
292 return errors::InvalidArgument(
293 "All input shapes must be fully defined.");
294 }
295 DimensionHandle unused;
296 if (!c->WithValue(c->Dim(c->input(i), 0), 1, &unused).ok()) {
297 return errors::InvalidArgument("Size of first dimension must be 1.");
298 }
299 TF_RETURN_WITH_CONTEXT_IF_ERROR(c->Merge(c->input(i), cur, &cur),
300 "From merging shape ", i,
301 " with other shapes.");
302 }
303
304 c->set_output(0, passed_shape);
305
306 return Status::OK();
307 });
308
309REGISTER_OP("Pack")
310 .Input("values: N * T")
311 .Output("output: T")
312 .Attr("N: int >= 1")
313 .Attr("T: type")
314 .Attr("axis: int = 0")
315 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
316 // Validate shapes of all inputs are compatible
317 ShapeHandle cur = c->input(c->num_inputs() - 1);
318 for (int i = c->num_inputs() - 2; i >= 0; --i) {
319 TF_RETURN_WITH_CONTEXT_IF_ERROR(c->Merge(c->input(i), cur, &cur),
320 "From merging shape ", i,
321 " with other shapes.");
322 }
323 if (!c->RankKnown(cur)) {
324 c->set_output(0, c->UnknownShape());
325 return Status::OK();
326 }
327 // Determine the axis that will be added, converting from negative
328 // axes to a positive point per negative indexing rules.
329 int32 rank = c->Rank(cur);
330 int32 axis;
331 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(GetAxisForPackAndUnpack(c, rank + 1, &axis));
332
333 // Copy all dimensions over, inserting a dimension of value #inputs
334 // at <axis>.
335 std::vector<DimensionHandle> dims;
336 int index = 0;
337 while (index < axis) dims.push_back(c->Dim(cur, index++));
338 dims.push_back(c->MakeDim(c->num_inputs()));
339 while (index < rank) dims.push_back(c->Dim(cur, index++));
340
341 c->set_output(0, c->MakeShape(dims));
342 return Status::OK();
343 });

389// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
390REGISTER_OP("Unpack")
391 .Input("value: T")
392 .Output("output: num * T")
393 .Attr("num: int >= 0")
394 .Attr("T: type")
395 .Attr("axis: int = 0")
396 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
397 ShapeHandle s = c->input(0);
398 ShapeHandle out;
399 if (c->RankKnown(s)) {
400 // Determine the axis that will be removed, converting from negative
401 // axes to a positive point per negative indexing rules.
402 int32 rank = c->Rank(s);
403 int32 axis;
404 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(GetAxisForPackAndUnpack(c, rank, &axis));
405
406 // The axis dim matches the number of outputs.
407 DimensionHandle unused;
408 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
409 c->WithValue(c->Dim(s, axis), c->num_outputs(), &unused));
410
411 // Copy all dimensions, removing the <axis> dimension.
412 std::vector<DimensionHandle> dims;
413 for (int i = 0; i < rank; ++i) {
414 if (i != axis) dims.push_back(c->Dim(s, i));
415 }
416 out = c->MakeShape(dims);
417 } else {
418 // All outputs are the same shape, but it's not known.
419 out = c->UnknownShape();
420 }
421 for (int i = 0; i < c->num_outputs(); ++i) c->set_output(i, out);
422 return Status::OK();
423 });

489REGISTER_OP("Split")
490 .Input("split_dim: int32")
491 .Input("value: T")
492 .Output("output: num_split * T")
493 .Attr("num_split: int >= 1")
494 .Attr("T: type")
495 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
496 DimensionHandle split_dimension;
497 ShapeHandle input = c->input(1);
498 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->MakeDimForScalarInputWithNegativeIndexing(
499 0, c->Rank(input), &split_dimension));
500 int num_split = c->num_outputs();
501 ShapeHandle out;
502 if (!c->ValueKnown(split_dimension)) {
503 if (c->RankKnown(input)) {
504 out = c->UnknownShapeOfRank(c->Rank(input));
505 } else {
506 out = c->UnknownShape();
507 }
508 } else {
509 int64 split_dim = c->Value(split_dimension);
510 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRankAtLeast(input, split_dim + 1, &input));
511 DimensionHandle split_dim_size;
512 TF_RETURN_WITH_CONTEXT_IF_ERROR(
513 c->Divide(c->Dim(input, split_dim), num_split,
514 true /* evenly_divisible */, &split_dim_size),
515 "Number of ways to split should evenly divide the split dimension");
516 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
517 c->ReplaceDim(input, split_dim, split_dim_size, &out));
518 }
519 for (int i = 0; i < num_split; ++i) c->set_output(i, out);
520 return Status::OK();
521 });
522
523REGISTER_OP("SplitV")
524 .Input("value: T")
525 .Input("size_splits: Tlen")
526 .Input("split_dim: int32")
527 .Output("output: num_split * T")
528 .Attr("num_split: int >= 1")
529 .Attr("T: type")
530 .Attr("Tlen: {int32, int64} = DT_INT64")
531 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
532 DimensionHandle split_dimension;
533 ShapeHandle input = c->input(0);
534 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->MakeDimForScalarInputWithNegativeIndexing(
535 2, c->Rank(input), &split_dimension));
536 int32 num_outputs = c->num_outputs();
537 int32 rank = c->Rank(input);
538 ShapeHandle output_shape;
539 const Tensor* size_splits = c->input_tensor(1);
540 if (rank == InferenceContext::kUnknownRank) {
541 // If the rank of input tensor is unknown, then return unknown shapes.
542 // Note that the shape of each output can be different.
543 for (int i = 0; i < num_outputs; ++i) {
544 c->set_output(i, c->UnknownShape());
545 }
546 } else if (rank == 0) {
547 // Throw error if input is a scalar.
548 return errors::InvalidArgument("Can't split scalars");
549 } else if (size_splits == nullptr && c->ValueKnown(split_dimension)) {
550 // If split dimension is known, but the sizes are unknown, then
551 // only the split dimension is unknown
552 output_shape = input;
553 for (int i = 0; i < num_outputs; ++i) {
554 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->ReplaceDim(output_shape,
555 c->Value(split_dimension),
556 c->UnknownDim(), &output_shape));
557 c->set_output(i, output_shape);
558 }
559 } else if (size_splits == nullptr && !c->ValueKnown(split_dimension)) {
560 // If split dimension or tensor containing the split sizes is unknown,
561 // then return unknown shapes of same rank as input. Note that each
562 // output shape can be different since splitv doesn't always split
563 // tensors evenly.
564 for (int i = 0; i < num_outputs; ++i) {
565 c->set_output(i, c->UnknownShapeOfRank(rank));
566 }
567 } else {
568 // Determine the output shape if split dimension and split sizes are
569 // known.
570 int64 split_dim = c->Value(split_dimension);
571 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRankAtLeast(input, split_dim + 1, &input));
572 std::vector<int64> data;
573 if (size_splits->dtype() == DT_INT32) {
574 data = AsInt64<int32>(size_splits, size_splits->shape().dim_size(0));
575 } else {
576 data = AsInt64<int64>(size_splits, size_splits->shape().dim_size(0));
577 }
578 if (num_outputs != data.size()) {
579 return errors::InvalidArgument(
580 "Length of size_splits should be equal to num_outputs");
581 }
582 int64_t cumsum_outputs = 0;
583 bool has_neg_one = false;
584 // If the sizes of the splits are known, then
585 // make sure that the sizes add up to the expected
586 // dimension size, with the possibility of a -1.
587 // Specify the full output shapes.
588 for (int i = 0; i < num_outputs; ++i) {
589 output_shape = c->UnknownShapeOfRank(rank);
590 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->ReplaceDim(input, split_dim,
591 c->MakeDim(data[i]), &output_shape));
592 c->set_output(i, output_shape);
593 if (data[i] == -1 && !has_neg_one)
594 has_neg_one = true;
595 else if (data[i] == -1 && has_neg_one)
596 return errors::InvalidArgument("size_splits can only have one -1");
597 else
598 cumsum_outputs += data[i];
599 }
600 auto split_dim_size = c->Value(c->Dim(input, split_dim));
601 if (has_neg_one) {
602 if (cumsum_outputs < split_dim_size)
603 cumsum_outputs = split_dim_size;
604 else
605 cumsum_outputs = split_dim_size + 1;
606 }
607 if (c->ValueKnown(c->Dim(input, split_dim)) &&
608 cumsum_outputs != c->Value(c->Dim(input, split_dim)))
609 return errors::InvalidArgument(
610 "Sum of output sizes must match "
611 "the size of the original Tensor along the split dimension "
612 "or the sum of the positive sizes must be less if it contains a "
613 "-1");
614 }
615
616 return Status::OK();
617 });

619// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
620REGISTER_OP("Const")
621 .Output("output: dtype")
622 .Attr("value: tensor")
623 .Attr("dtype: type")
624 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
625 const TensorProto* proto = nullptr;
626 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->GetAttr("value", &proto));
627 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(TensorShape::IsValidShape(proto->tensor_shape()));
628 TensorShape shape(proto->tensor_shape());
629 std::vector<DimensionHandle> dims;
630 dims.reserve(shape.dims());
631 for (int i = 0; i < shape.dims(); ++i) {
632 dims.push_back(c->MakeDim(shape.dim_size(i)));
633 }
634 c->set_output(0, c->MakeShape(dims));
635 return Status::OK();

674// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
675REGISTER_OP("Diag")
676 .Input("diagonal: T")
677 .Output("output: T")
678 .Attr(
679 "T: {bfloat16, half, float, double, int32, int64, complex64, "
680 "complex128}")
681 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
682 ShapeHandle in = c->input(0);
683 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRankAtLeast(in, 1, &in));
684 // Output shape is original concatenated with itself.
685 ShapeHandle out;
686 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Concatenate(in, in, &out));
687 c->set_output(0, out);
688 return Status::OK();

691// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
692REGISTER_OP("DiagPart")
693 .Input("input: T")
694 .Output("diagonal: T")
695 .Attr(
696 "T: {bfloat16, half, float, double, int32, int64, complex64, "
697 "complex128}")
698 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
699 ShapeHandle in = c->input(0);
700 if (!c->RankKnown(in)) {
701 c->set_output(0, c->UnknownShape());
702 return Status::OK();
703 }
704 // Rank must be even, and result will have rank <rank/2>.
705 const int32 rank = c->Rank(in);
706 if ((rank % 2) != 0 || rank <= 0) {
707 return errors::InvalidArgument(
708 "Input must have even and non-zero rank, input rank is ", rank);
709 }
710 const int32 mid = rank / 2;
711
712 // output dim[i] is the merge of in.dim[i] and in.dim[i+mid].
713 std::vector<DimensionHandle> dims(mid);
714 for (int i = 0; i < mid; ++i) {
715 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
716 c->Merge(c->Dim(in, i), c->Dim(in, i + mid), &dims[i]));
717 }
718 c->set_output(0, c->MakeShape(dims));
719 return Status::OK();
720 });
721
722// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
723REGISTER_OP("MatrixDiag")
724 .Input("diagonal: T")
725 .Output("output: T")
726 .Attr("T: type")
727 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
728 ShapeHandle in;
729 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRankAtLeast(c->input(0), 1, &in));
730 if (!c->RankKnown(in)) {
731 c->set_output(0, c->UnknownShape());
732 return Status::OK();
733 }
734 const int32 rank = c->Rank(in);
735 ShapeHandle out;
736 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
737 c->Concatenate(in, c->Vector(c->Dim(in, rank - 1)), &out));
738 c->set_output(0, out);
739 return Status::OK();
740 });
741
742// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
743REGISTER_OP("MatrixSetDiag")
744 .Input("input: T")
745 .Input("diagonal: T")
746 .Output("output: T")
747 .Attr("T: type")
748 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
749 ShapeHandle input;
750 ShapeHandle diag;
751 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRankAtLeast(c->input(0), 2, &input));
752 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRankAtLeast(c->input(1), 1, &diag));
753 if (c->RankKnown(input)) {
754 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(c->input(1), c->Rank(input) - 1, &diag));
755 }
756 DimensionHandle smallest_dim;
757 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
758 c->Min(c->Dim(input, -2), c->Dim(input, -1), &smallest_dim));
759 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
760 c->Merge(smallest_dim, c->Dim(diag, -1), &smallest_dim));
761
762 ShapeHandle output = input;
763 if (c->RankKnown(diag) && !c->FullyDefined(input)) {
764 // Try to infer parts of shape from diag.
765 ShapeHandle diag_prefix;
766 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Subshape(diag, 0, -1, &diag_prefix));
767 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
768 c->Concatenate(diag_prefix, c->UnknownShapeOfRank(2), &diag));
769 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Merge(input, diag, &output));
770 }
771 c->set_output(0, output);
772 return Status::OK();
773 });

775// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
776REGISTER_OP("MatrixDiagPart")
777 .Input("input: T")
778 .Output("diagonal: T")
779 .Attr("T: type")
780 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
781 ShapeHandle in;
782 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRankAtLeast(c->input(0), 2, &in));
783 if (!c->RankKnown(in)) {
784 c->set_output(0, c->UnknownShape());
785 return Status::OK();
786 }
787 const int32 rank = c->Rank(in);
788 std::vector<DimensionHandle> dims;
789 dims.reserve(rank - 2);
790 for (int i = 0; i < rank - 2; ++i) dims.push_back(c->Dim(in, i));
791
792 DimensionHandle min_dim;
793 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
794 c->Min(c->Dim(in, rank - 2), c->Dim(in, rank - 1), &min_dim));
795 dims.push_back(min_dim);
796 c->set_output(0, c->MakeShape(dims));
797 return Status::OK();
798 });

810// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
811REGISTER_OP("Reverse")
812 .Input("tensor: T")
813 .Input("dims: bool")
814 .Output("output: T")
815 .Attr(
816 "T: {uint8, int8, uint16, int16, int32, int64, bool, half, "
817 "float, double, complex64, complex128, string}")
818 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
819 ShapeHandle input = c->input(0);
820 ShapeHandle dims;
821 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(c->input(1), 1, &dims));
822 DimensionHandle dims_dim = c->Dim(dims, 0);
823 if (c->ValueKnown(dims_dim)) {
824 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(input, c->Value(dims_dim), &input));
825 }
826 if (c->Rank(input) > 8) {
827 return errors::InvalidArgument(
828 "reverse does not work on tensors with more than 8 dimensions");
829 }
830 c->set_output(0, input);
831 return Status::OK();
832 });

834// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
835REGISTER_OP("ReverseV2")
836 .Input("tensor: T")
837 .Input("axis: Tidx")
838 .Output("output: T")
839 .Attr("Tidx: {int32, int64} = DT_INT32")
840 .Attr(
841 "T: {uint8, int8, uint16, int16, int32, int64, bool, bfloat16, half, "
842 "float, double, complex64, complex128, string}")
843 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
844 ShapeHandle input = c->input(0);
845 ShapeHandle axis;
846 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(c->input(1), 1, &axis));
847 if (c->Rank(input) > 8) {
848 return errors::InvalidArgument(
849 "reverse does not work on tensors with more than 8 dimensions");
850 }
851 const Tensor* axis_tensor = c->input_tensor(1);
852 if (axis_tensor != nullptr && c->RankKnown(input)) {
853 int32 rank = c->Rank(input);
854 std::vector<int64> axis_value;
855 if (axis_tensor->dtype() == DT_INT32) {
856 axis_value = AsInt64<int32>(axis_tensor, axis_tensor->NumElements());
857 } else {
858 axis_value = AsInt64<int64>(axis_tensor, axis_tensor->NumElements());
859 }
860 std::vector<bool> axes_dense(c->Rank(input), false);
861 for (int i = 0; i < axis_value.size(); i++) {
862 int64 canonical_axis =
863 axis_value[i] < 0 ? rank + axis_value[i] : axis_value[i];
864 if (canonical_axis < 0 || canonical_axis >= rank) {
865 return errors::InvalidArgument("'axis'[", i, "] = ", axis_value[i],
866 " is out of valid range [", 0, ", ",
867 rank - 1);
868 }
869 if (axes_dense[canonical_axis]) {
870 return errors::InvalidArgument("axis ", canonical_axis,
871 " specified more than once.");
872 }
873 axes_dense[canonical_axis] = true;
874 }
875 }
876 c->set_output(0, input);
877 return Status::OK();
878 });
879
880// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
881REGISTER_OP("EditDistance")
882 .Input("hypothesis_indices: int64")
883 .Input("hypothesis_values: T")
884 .Input("hypothesis_shape: int64")
885 .Input("truth_indices: int64")
886 .Input("truth_values: T")
887 .Input("truth_shape: int64")
888 .Attr("normalize: bool = true")
889 .Attr("T: type")
890 .Output("output: float")
891 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
892 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(shape_inference::ValidateSparseTensor(
893 c, c->input(0), c->input(1), c->input(2)));
894 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(shape_inference::ValidateSparseTensor(
895 c, c->input(3), c->input(4), c->input(5)));
896 const Tensor* hypothesis_shape_t = c->input_tensor(2);
897 const Tensor* truth_shape_t = c->input_tensor(5);
898 if (hypothesis_shape_t == nullptr || truth_shape_t == nullptr) {
899 // We need to know the runtime shape of the two tensors,
900 // or else the output shape is unknown.
901 return shape_inference::UnknownShape(c);
902 }
903
904 if (hypothesis_shape_t->NumElements() != truth_shape_t->NumElements()) {
905 return errors::InvalidArgument(
906 "Num elements of hypothesis_shape does not match truth_shape: ",
907 hypothesis_shape_t->NumElements(), " vs. ",
908 truth_shape_t->NumElements());
909 }
910
911 auto h_values = hypothesis_shape_t->flat<int64>();
912 auto t_values = truth_shape_t->flat<int64>();
913 std::vector<DimensionHandle> dims(hypothesis_shape_t->NumElements() - 1);
914 for (int i = 0; i < dims.size(); ++i) {
915 dims[i] = c->MakeDim(std::max(h_values(i), t_values(i)));
916 }
917
918 c->set_output(0, c->MakeShape(dims));
919 return Status::OK();
920 });

922// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
923REGISTER_OP("Fill")
924 .Input("dims: index_type")
925 .Input("value: T")
926 .Output("output: T")
927 .Attr("T: type")
928 .Attr("index_type: {int32, int64} = DT_INT32")
929 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
930 DataType index_type = DT_INT32;
931 Status s = c->GetAttr("index_type", &index_type);
932 if (!s.ok() && s.code() != error::NOT_FOUND) {
933 return s;
934 }
935 ShapeHandle unused;
936 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(c->input(0), 1, &unused));
937 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(c->input(1), 0, &unused));
938
939 const Tensor* t = c->input_tensor(0);
940 if (t != nullptr) {
941 for (int i = 0; i < t->NumElements(); ++i) {
942 if ((index_type == DT_INT32 && t->vec<int32>()(i) < 0) ||
943 (index_type == DT_INT64 && t->vec<int64>()(i) < 0)) {
944 return errors::InvalidArgument("Fill dimensions must be >= 0");
945 }
946 }
947 }
948
949 ShapeHandle out;
950 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->MakeShapeFromShapeTensor(0, &out));
951 c->set_output(0, out);
952 return Status::OK();
953 });

997// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
998REGISTER_OP("Gather")
999 .Input("params: Tparams")
1000 .Input("indices: Tindices")
1001 .Attr("validate_indices: bool = true")
1002 .Output("output: Tparams")
1003 .Attr("Tparams: type")
1004 .Attr("Tindices: {int32,int64}")
1005 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
1006 ShapeHandle unused;
1007 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRankAtLeast(c->input(0), 1, &unused));
1008 ShapeHandle params_subshape;
1009 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Subshape(c->input(0), 1, &params_subshape));
1010 ShapeHandle indices_shape = c->input(1);
1011 ShapeHandle out;
1012 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Concatenate(indices_shape, params_subshape, &out));
1013 c->set_output(0, out);
1014 return Status::OK();
1015 });
1016
1017// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
1018REGISTER_OP("GatherV2")
1019 .Input("params: Tparams")
1020 .Input("indices: Tindices")
1021 .Input("axis: Taxis")
1022 .Output("output: Tparams")
1023 .Attr("Tparams: type")
1024 .Attr("Tindices: {int32,int64}")
1025 .Attr("Taxis: {int32,int64}")
1026 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
1027 ShapeHandle params_shape;
1028 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRankAtLeast(c->input(0), 1, &params_shape));
1029
1030 ShapeHandle indices_shape = c->input(1);
1031 ShapeHandle unused_axis_shape;
1032 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(c->input(2), 0, &unused_axis_shape));
1033 const Tensor* axis_t = c->input_tensor(2);
1034
1035 // If axis is unknown, we can only infer that the result is params_rank +
1036 // indices_rank - 1.
1037 if (axis_t == nullptr) {
1038 if (c->RankKnown(params_shape) && c->RankKnown(indices_shape)) {
1039 c->set_output(0, c->UnknownShapeOfRank(c->Rank(params_shape) +
1040 c->Rank(indices_shape) - 1));
1041 } else {
1042 c->set_output(0, c->UnknownShape());
1043 }
1044 return Status::OK();
1045 }
1046
1047 // Note, axis can be negative.
1048 int64 axis = 0;
1049 if (axis_t->dtype() == DT_INT32) {
1050 axis = axis_t->scalar<int32>()();
1051 } else {
1052 axis = axis_t->scalar<int64>()();
1053 }
1054
1055 // Check that params has rank of at least axis + 1.
1056 ShapeHandle unused;
1057 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRankAtLeast(
1058 params_shape, axis < 0 ? -axis : axis + 1, &unused));
1059
1060 ShapeHandle params_outer_subshape;
1061 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
1062 c->Subshape(params_shape, 0, axis, &params_outer_subshape));
1063
1064 ShapeHandle out;
1065 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
1066 c->Concatenate(params_outer_subshape, indices_shape, &out));
1067
1068 // Slice from axis + 1 to the end of params_shape to collect the inner
1069 // dimensions of the result. Special case -1 here since -1 + 1 wraps, and
1070 // we slice from 0 to the end of shape. Subshape() handles all other
1071 // out-of-bounds checking.
1072 if (axis != -1) {
1073 ShapeHandle params_inner_subshape;
1074 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
1075 c->Subshape(params_shape, axis + 1, &params_inner_subshape));
1076 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Concatenate(out, params_inner_subshape, &out));
1077 }
1078
1079 c->set_output(0, out);
1080 return Status::OK();
1081 });
1082
1083// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
1084REGISTER_OP("GatherNd")
1085 .Input("params: Tparams")
1086 .Input("indices: Tindices")
1087 .Output("output: Tparams")
1088 .Attr("Tparams: type")
1089 .Attr("Tindices: {int32,int64}")
1090 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
1091 ShapeHandle params = c->input(0);
1092 ShapeHandle indices;
1093 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRankAtLeast(c->input(1), 1, &indices));
1094 DimensionHandle r_dim = c->Dim(indices, -1);
1095
1096 if (!c->RankKnown(params) || !c->ValueKnown(r_dim)) {
1097 c->set_output(0, c->UnknownShape());
1098 return Status::OK();
1099 }
1100
1101 if (c->Value(r_dim) > c->Rank(params)) {
1102 return errors::InvalidArgument(
1103 "indices.shape[-1] must be <= params.rank, but saw indices shape: ",
1104 c->DebugString(indices),
1105 " and params shape: ", c->DebugString(params));
1106 }
1107
1108 // Remove r_dim from indices to get output.
1109 ShapeHandle indices_slice;
1110 ShapeHandle params_slice;
1111 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Subshape(indices, 0, -1, &indices_slice));
1112 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Subshape(params, c->Value(r_dim), &params_slice));
1113 ShapeHandle out;
1114 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Concatenate(indices_slice, params_slice, &out));
1115 c->set_output(0, out);
1116 return Status::OK();
1117 });

1339namespace {
1340
1341Status ShapeShapeFn(InferenceContext* c) {
1342 for (int i = 0; i < c->num_inputs(); ++i) {
1343 DimensionHandle dim;
1344 if (c->RankKnown(c->input(i))) {
1345 dim = c->MakeDim(c->Rank(c->input(i)));
1346 } else {
1347 dim = c->UnknownDim();
1348 }
1349 c->set_output(i, c->Vector(dim));
1350 }
1351 return Status::OK();
1352}
1353
1354} // namespace

1372// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
1373REGISTER_OP("ReverseSequence")
1374 .Input("input: T")
1375 .Input("seq_lengths: Tlen")
1376 .Output("output: T")
1377 .Attr("seq_dim: int")
1378 .Attr("batch_dim: int = 0")
1379 .Attr("T: type")
1380 .Attr("Tlen: {int32, int64} = DT_INT64")
1381 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
1382 ShapeHandle input = c->input(0);
1383 ShapeHandle seq_lens_shape;
1384 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(c->input(1), 1, &seq_lens_shape));
1385
1386 int64 seq_dim;
1387 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->GetAttr("seq_dim", &seq_dim));
1388 int64 batch_dim;
1389 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->GetAttr("batch_dim", &batch_dim));
1390
1391 if (!c->RankKnown(input)) {
1392 return shape_inference::UnknownShape(c);
1393 }
1394
1395 // Validate batch_dim and seq_dim against input.
1396 const int32 input_rank = c->Rank(input);
1397 if (batch_dim >= input_rank) {
1398 return errors::InvalidArgument(
1399 "batch_dim must be < input rank: ", batch_dim, " vs. ", input_rank);
1400 }
1401 if (seq_dim >= input_rank) {
1402 return errors::InvalidArgument(
1403 "seq_dim must be < input rank: ", seq_dim, " vs. ", input_rank);
1404 }
1405
1406 DimensionHandle batch_dim_dim = c->Dim(input, batch_dim);
1407 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
1408 c->Merge(batch_dim_dim, c->Dim(seq_lens_shape, 0), &batch_dim_dim));
1409
1410 // Replace batch_dim of input with batch_size
1411 ShapeHandle output_shape;
1412 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
1413 c->ReplaceDim(input, batch_dim, batch_dim_dim, &output_shape));
1414 c->set_output(0, output_shape);
1415 return Status::OK();
1416 });

1421 .Output("output: int32")
1422 .Attr("T: type")
1423 .SetShapeFn(shape_inference::ScalarShape);

1433namespace {
1434
1435// This SliceHelper processes the output shape of the `slice`
1436// when the tensor of `sizes` is available.
1437template <typename T>
1438Status SliceHelper(InferenceContext* c, ShapeHandle begin_value,
1439 const Tensor* sizes_value,
1440 std::vector<DimensionHandle>* dims) {
1441 auto sizes_vec = sizes_value->vec<T>();
1442 for (int i = 0; i < sizes_value->NumElements(); ++i) {
1443 DimensionHandle dim = c->Dim(c->input(0), i);
1444 if (sizes_vec(i) != -1) {
1445 auto dim_val = c->Value(dim);
1446 if (sizes_vec(i) < 0) {
1447 return errors::InvalidArgument(
1448 "Out of bounds slicing on dimension ", i, " of length ", dim_val,
1449 ": sizes vector cannot be < -1, but was ", sizes_vec(i));
1450 }
1451
1452 dims->emplace_back(c->MakeDim(sizes_vec(i)));
1453 } else {
1454 DimensionHandle result;
1455 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Subtract(dim, c->Dim(begin_value, i), &result));
1456 dims->emplace_back(result);
1457 }
1458 }
1459
1460 return Status::OK();
1461}
1462} // namespace
1463
1464// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
1465REGISTER_OP("Slice")
1466 .Input("input: T")
1467 .Input("begin: Index")
1468 .Input("size: Index")
1469 .Output("output: T")
1470 .Attr("T: type")
1471 .Attr("Index: {int32,int64}")
1472 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
1473 ShapeHandle input = c->input(0);
1474 ShapeHandle begin_shape;
1475 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(c->input(1), 1, &begin_shape));
1476 ShapeHandle sizes_shape;
1477 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(c->input(2), 1, &sizes_shape));
1478
1479 // Merge to check compatibility of begin and sizes tensors.
1480 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Merge(begin_shape, sizes_shape, &begin_shape));
1481
1482 DimensionHandle ndims = c->Dim(begin_shape, 0);
1483 if (c->ValueKnown(ndims)) {
1484 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(input, c->Value(ndims), &input));
1485 }
1486
1487 // NOTE(mrry): Use MakeShapeFromShapeTensor to handle partially-known
1488 // values, even though the `begin` value does not represent a shape.
1489 ShapeHandle begin_value;
1490 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->MakeShapeFromShapeTensor(1, &begin_value));
1491
1492 // We check the tensor value here and will only use
1493 // `MakeShapeFromShapeTensor` when `sizes_value` is null.
1494 // The reason is that `sizes`might contain -1, which can't
1495 // be represented (-1 in the ShapeHandle would mean "unknown".
1496 const Tensor* sizes_value = c->input_tensor(2);
1497
1498 if (sizes_value != nullptr) {
1499 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
1500 c->WithRank(begin_value, sizes_value->NumElements(), &begin_value));
1501 std::vector<DimensionHandle> dims;
1502 // If the begin and sizes tensors are available, then
1503 // we can be precise about the shape of the output.
1504 if (sizes_value->dtype() == DT_INT64) {
1505 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
1506 SliceHelper<int64>(c, begin_value, sizes_value, &dims));
1507 } else {
1508 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
1509 SliceHelper<int32>(c, begin_value, sizes_value, &dims));
1510 }
1511
1512 c->set_output(0, c->MakeShape(dims));
1513 return Status::OK();
1514 } else {
1515 // In case `sizes` is not available (`sizes_value` is null),
1516 // we could try to use `MakeShapeFromShapeTensor` here.
1517 // If sizes contain -1, we will simply consider it as `Unknown`.
1518 // This is less than ideal but still an improvement of shape inference.
1519 // The following is an example that returns [None, 1, None] with this
1520 // code path:
1521 // z = tf.zeros((1, 2, 3))
1522 // m = tf.slice(z, [0, 0, 0], [tf.constant(1) + 0, 1, -1])
1523 // m.get_shape().as_list()
1524 ShapeHandle sizes_value;
1525 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->MakeShapeFromShapeTensor(2, &sizes_value));
1526 if (c->RankKnown(sizes_value)) {
1527 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
1528 c->WithRank(begin_value, c->Rank(sizes_value), &begin_value));
1529 std::vector<DimensionHandle> dims;
1530 dims.reserve(c->Rank(sizes_value));
1531 for (int i = 0; i < c->Rank(sizes_value); ++i) {
1532 dims.emplace_back(c->Dim(sizes_value, i));
1533 }
1534 c->set_output(0, c->MakeShape(dims));
1535 return Status::OK();
1536 }
1537
1538 // We might know the rank of the input.
1539 if (c->RankKnown(input)) {
1540 c->set_output(0, c->UnknownShapeOfRank(c->Rank(input)));
1541 return Status::OK();
1542 } else {
1543 return shape_inference::UnknownShape(c);
1544 }
1545 }
1546
1547 return Status::OK();
1548 });
1549
1550REGISTER_OP("StridedSlice")
1551 .Input("input: T")
1552 .Input("begin: Index")
1553 .Input("end: Index")
1554 .Input("strides: Index")
1555 .Output("output: T")
1556 .Attr("T: type")
1557 .Attr("Index: {int32, int64}")
1558 .Attr("begin_mask: int = 0")
1559 .Attr("end_mask: int = 0")
1560 .Attr("ellipsis_mask: int = 0")
1561 .Attr("new_axis_mask: int = 0")
1562 .Attr("shrink_axis_mask: int = 0")
1563 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
1564 ShapeHandle input = c->input(0);
1565 ShapeHandle begin_shape, end_shape, strides_shape;
1566 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(c->input(1), 1, &begin_shape));
1567 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(c->input(2), 1, &end_shape));
1568 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(c->input(3), 1, &strides_shape));
1569 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Merge(begin_shape, end_shape, &begin_shape));
1570 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Merge(begin_shape, strides_shape, &begin_shape));
1571 DimensionHandle sparse_dims_dim = c->Dim(begin_shape, 0);
1572
1573 const Tensor* strides_value = c->input_tensor(3);
1574 // TODO(aselle,allenl): If we had a stride_mask it would be possible to do
1575 // more shape inference here (e.g. for x[3, ::T]).
1576 if (!c->RankKnown(input) || !c->ValueKnown(sparse_dims_dim) ||
1577 strides_value == nullptr) {
1578 c->set_output(0, c->UnknownShape());
1579 return Status::OK();
1580 }
1581
1582 PartialTensorShape input_shape({});
1583 for (int i = 0; i < c->Rank(input); ++i) {
1584 auto dim = c->Dim(input, i);
1585 input_shape.AddDim(c->ValueKnown(dim) ? c->Value(dim) : -1);
1586 }
1587
1588 int32 begin_mask, end_mask, ellipsis_mask, new_axis_mask,
1589 shrink_axis_mask;
1590 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->GetAttr("begin_mask", &begin_mask));
1591 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->GetAttr("end_mask", &end_mask));
1592 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->GetAttr("ellipsis_mask", &ellipsis_mask));
1593 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->GetAttr("new_axis_mask", &new_axis_mask));
1594 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->GetAttr("shrink_axis_mask", &shrink_axis_mask));
1595
1596 const Tensor* begin_value = c->input_tensor(1);
1597 const Tensor* end_value = c->input_tensor(2);
1598
1599 PartialTensorShape processing_shape, final_shape;
1600 bool is_identity, is_simple_slice, slice_dim0;
1601 gtl::InlinedVector<int64, 4> begin, end, strides;
1602 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(ValidateStridedSliceOp(
1603 begin_value, end_value, *strides_value, input_shape, begin_mask,
1604 end_mask, ellipsis_mask, new_axis_mask, shrink_axis_mask,
1605 &processing_shape, &final_shape, &is_identity, &is_simple_slice,
1606 &slice_dim0, &begin, &end, &strides));
1607
1608 ShapeHandle out;
1609 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->MakeShapeFromPartialTensorShape(final_shape, &out));
1610 c->set_output(0, out);
1611
1612 return Status::OK();
1613 });

1670REGISTER_OP("Tile")
1671 .Input("input: T")
1672 .Input("multiples: Tmultiples")
1673 .Output("output: T")
1674 .Attr("T: type")
1675 .Attr("Tmultiples: {int32, int64} = DT_INT32")
1676 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
1677 ShapeHandle input = c->input(0);
1678 // NOTE(mrry): Represent `multiples` as a `TensorShape` because (i)
1679 // it is a vector of non-negative integers, and (ii) doing so allows
1680 // us to handle partially-known multiples.
1681 ShapeHandle multiples;
1682 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->MakeShapeFromShapeTensor(1, &multiples));
1683 if (c->RankKnown(input)) {
1684 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(multiples, c->Rank(input), &multiples));
1685 ShapeHandle dummy;
1686 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
1687 c->Merge(c->input(1), c->Vector(c->Rank(input)), &dummy));
1688 }
1689
1690 if (!c->RankKnown(multiples)) {
1691 return shape_inference::UnknownShape(c);
1692 }
1693
1694 int32 rank = c->Rank(multiples);
1695 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(input, rank, &input));
1696 std::vector<DimensionHandle> dims(rank);
1697 for (int i = 0; i < rank; ++i) {
1698 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
1699 c->Multiply(c->Dim(input, i), c->Dim(multiples, i), &dims[i]));
1700 }
1701 c->set_output(0, c->MakeShape(dims));
1702 return Status::OK();
1703 });

1725REGISTER_OP("BroadcastArgs")
1726 .Input("s0: T")
1727 .Input("s1: T")
1728 .Output("r0: T")
1729 .Attr("T: {int32, int64} = DT_INT32")
1730 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
1731 ShapeHandle unused;

1733 ShapeHandle shape_y = c->input(1);
1734 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(shape_x, 1, &unused));
1735 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(shape_y, 1, &unused));

1738 !c->ValueKnown(c->Dim(shape_y, 0))) {
1739 c->set_output(0, c->Vector(InferenceContext::kUnknownDim));
1740 return Status::OK();
1741 }
1742
1743 int64 x_dim = c->Value(c->Dim(shape_x, 0));
1744 int64 y_dim = c->Value(c->Dim(shape_y, 0));
1745
1746 // Broadcasted shape is going to be as large as the largest dimension.
1747 c->set_output(0, c->Vector(std::max(x_dim, y_dim)));
1748 return Status::OK();
1749 });

1788REGISTER_OP("MirrorPad")
1789 .Input("input: T")
1790 .Input("paddings: Tpaddings")
1791 .Output("output: T")
1792 .Attr("T: type")
1793 .Attr("Tpaddings: {int32, int64} = DT_INT32")
1794 .Attr(GetMirrorPadModeAttrString())
1795 .SetShapeFn(PadShapeFn);
1796
1797// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
1798namespace {
1799template <typename T>
1800Status MirrorPadKnown(InferenceContext* c, ShapeHandle input,
1801 const Tensor* paddings_t, int64 input_rank) {
1802 auto paddings_data = paddings_t->matrix<T>();
1803 std::vector<DimensionHandle> dims(input_rank);
1804 for (int64 i = 0; i < input_rank; ++i) {
1805 const int64 pad0 = static_cast<int64>(paddings_data(i, 0));
1806 const int64 pad1 = static_cast<int64>(paddings_data(i, 1));
1807 if (pad0 < 0 || pad1 < 0) {
1808 return errors::InvalidArgument("Paddings must be non-negative");
1809 }
1810
1811 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Subtract(c->Dim(input, i), pad0 + pad1, &dims[i]));
1812 }
1813 c->set_output(0, c->MakeShape(dims));
1814 return Status::OK();
1815}
1816
1817} // namespace
1818
1819REGISTER_OP("MirrorPadGrad")
1820 .Input("input: T")
1821 .Input("paddings: Tpaddings")
1822 .Output("output: T")
1823 .Attr("T: type")
1824 .Attr("Tpaddings: {int32, int64} = DT_INT32")
1825 .Attr(GetMirrorPadModeAttrString())
1826 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
1827 ShapeHandle paddings;
1828 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(c->input(1), 2, &paddings));
1829 DimensionHandle pad_0 = c->Dim(paddings, 0);
1830 if (!c->ValueKnown(pad_0)) {
1831 // We don't know the rank of the output since the first
1832 // padding dimension is unknown.
1833 c->set_output(0, c->UnknownShape());
1834 return Status::OK();
1835 }
1836
1837 int64 input_rank = c->Value(pad_0);
1838 ShapeHandle input;
1839 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(c->input(0), input_rank, &input));
1840 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
1841 c->Merge(paddings, c->Matrix(input_rank, 2), &paddings));
1842
1843 const Tensor* paddings_t = c->input_tensor(1);
1844 if (paddings_t == nullptr) {
1845 // Values of 'paddings' is not available, but we know the
1846 // input rank, so return the rank of the output with unknown
1847 // dimensions.
1848 c->set_output(0, c->UnknownShapeOfRank(input_rank));
1849 return Status::OK();
1850 }
1851
1852 if (paddings_t->dtype() == DT_INT32) {
1853 return MirrorPadKnown<int32>(c, input, paddings_t, input_rank);
1854 } else {
1855 return MirrorPadKnown<int64>(c, input, paddings_t, input_rank);
1856 }
1857 });

1860REGISTER_OP("Placeholder")
1861 .Output("output: dtype")
1862 .Attr("dtype: type")
1863 .Attr("shape: shape = { unknown_rank: true }")
1864 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
1865 PartialTensorShape shape;
1866 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->GetAttr("shape", &shape));
1867
1868 // Placeholder has legacy behavior where we cannot tell the difference
1869 // between a scalar shape attribute and 'unknown shape'. So if the shape
1870 // is a scalar, we return an unknown shape.
1871 if (c->graph_def_version() <= 21 && shape.dims() <= 0) {
1872 return shape_inference::UnknownShape(c);
1873 }
1874
1875 ShapeHandle out;
1876 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->MakeShapeFromPartialTensorShape(shape, &out));
1877 c->set_output(0, out);
1878 return Status::OK();
1879 });

1893 .Input("input: dtype")
1894 .Output("output: dtype")
1895 .Attr("dtype: type")

1897 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {

1900 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->GetAttr("shape", &shape));
1901 ShapeHandle out;
1902 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->MakeShapeFromPartialTensorShape(shape, &out));
1903

1905 // since output_shape may be less precise than input_shape.

1908 c->set_output(0, out);

1912// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
1913REGISTER_OP("ExpandDims")
1914 .Input("input: T")
1915 .Input("dim: Tdim")
1916 .Output("output: T")
1917 .Attr("T: type")
1918 .Attr("Tdim: {int32, int64} = DT_INT32")
1919 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
1920 ShapeHandle input = c->input(0);
1921
1922 const Tensor* dim_t = c->input_tensor(1);
1923 if (dim_t != nullptr && dim_t->NumElements() != 1) {
1924 return errors::InvalidArgument(
1925 "'dim' input must be a tensor with a single value");
1926 }
1927 if (dim_t == nullptr || !c->RankKnown(input)) {
1928 c->set_output(0, c->UnknownShape());
1929 return Status::OK();
1930 }
1931
1932 int64 dim;
1933 if (dim_t->dtype() == DT_INT32) {
1934 dim = static_cast<int64>(dim_t->flat<int32>()(0));
1935 } else {
1936 dim = dim_t->flat<int64>()(0);
1937 }
1938
1939 const int32 rank = c->Rank(input);
1940 const int32 min_dim = -1 * rank - 1;
1941 if (dim < min_dim || dim > rank) {
1942 return errors::InvalidArgument("dim ", dim, " not in the interval [",
1943 min_dim, ", ", rank, "].");
1944 }
1945
1946 if (dim < 0) {
1947 dim += rank + 1;
1948 }
1949
1950 ShapeHandle end;
1951 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Subshape(input, dim, &end));
1952
1953 // Build output as start + 1 + end.
1954 ShapeHandle output;
1955 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Subshape(input, 0, dim, &output));
1956 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Concatenate(output, c->Vector(1), &output));
1957 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Concatenate(output, end, &output));
1958 c->set_output(0, output);
1959 return Status::OK();
1960 });
1961
1962// --------------------------------------------------------------------------
1963REGISTER_OP("Squeeze")
1964 .Input("input: T")
1965 .Output("output: T")
1966 .Attr("T: type")
1967 .Attr("squeeze_dims: list(int) >= 0 = []")
1968 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
1969 ShapeHandle input = c->input(0);
1970 if (!c->RankKnown(input)) {
1971 // Input shape unknown.
1972 return shape_inference::UnknownShape(c);
1973 }
1974
1975 const int32 input_rank = c->Rank(input);
1976
1977 // Validate and wrap squeeze dimensions.
1978 std::vector<int32> squeeze_dims;
1979 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->GetAttr("squeeze_dims", &squeeze_dims));
1980 for (int i = 0; i < squeeze_dims.size(); ++i) {
1981 if (squeeze_dims[i] < -input_rank || squeeze_dims[i] >= input_rank) {
1982 return errors::InvalidArgument("squeeze_dims[", i, "] not in [",
1983 -input_rank, ",", input_rank, ").");
1984 }
1985
1986 if (squeeze_dims[i] < 0) {
1987 squeeze_dims[i] += input_rank;
1988 }
1989 }
1990
1991 std::vector<DimensionHandle> result_shape;
1992 for (int i = 0; i < input_rank; ++i) {
1993 // True if squeeze_dims contains an entry to squeeze this
1994 // dimension.
1995 bool is_explicit_match =
1996 std::find(squeeze_dims.begin(), squeeze_dims.end(), i) !=
1997 squeeze_dims.end();
1998
1999 DimensionHandle dim = c->Dim(input, i);
2000
2001 if (!c->ValueKnown(dim)) {
2002 // Assume that the squeezed dimension will be 1 at runtime.
2003 if (is_explicit_match) continue;
2004
2005 // If squeezing all 1 dimensions, and we see an unknown value,
2006 // give up and return Unknown Shape.
2007 if (squeeze_dims.empty()) {
2008 c->set_output(0, c->UnknownShape());
2009 return Status::OK();
2010 }
2011 } else if (c->Value(dim) == 1) {
2012 if (is_explicit_match || squeeze_dims.empty()) {
2013 // If explicitly squeezing, or squeezing all 1s, remove
2014 // this dimension.
2015 continue;
2016 }
2017 } else if (is_explicit_match) {
2018 return errors::InvalidArgument("Can not squeeze dim[", i,
2019 "], expected a dimension of 1, got ",
2020 c->Value(c->Dim(input, i)));
2021 }
2022
2023 result_shape.emplace_back(dim);
2024 }
2025
2026 c->set_output(0, c->MakeShape(result_shape));
2027 return Status::OK();
2028 });

2035 .Output("idx: out_idx")

2051// Converts Tensor to flat std::vector<int64>.
2052template <typename InputType>
2053std::vector<int64> GetFlatInt64(const Tensor& t) {
2054 std::vector<int64> output(t.shape().num_elements());
2055 auto eigen_vec = t.flat<InputType>();
2056 std::copy_n(&eigen_vec(0), output.size(), output.begin());
2057 return output;
2058}
2059
2060// Converts int32 or int64 Tensor to flat std::vector<int64>.
2061std::vector<int64> GetFlatInt64(const Tensor& t) {
2062 if (t.dtype() == DT_INT32) {
2063 return GetFlatInt64<int32>(t);
2064 } else {
2065 return GetFlatInt64<int64>(t);
2066 }
2067}
2068
2069Status SpaceToBatchShapeHelper(InferenceContext* c, ShapeHandle input_shape,
2070 ShapeHandle block_shape_shape,
2071 const Tensor* block_shape_t,
2072 ShapeHandle paddings_shape,
2073 const Tensor* paddings_t) {
2074 if (c->Rank(block_shape_shape) != 1) {
2075 return errors::InvalidArgument("block_shape must have rank 1.");
2076 }
2077
2078 const DimensionHandle num_block_dims_handle = c->Dim(block_shape_shape, 0);
2079 if (!c->ValueKnown(num_block_dims_handle)) {
2080 return errors::InvalidArgument("block_shape must have known size.");
2081 }
2082
2083 const int64 num_block_dims = c->Value(num_block_dims_handle);
2084
2085 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2086 c->WithRankAtLeast(input_shape, num_block_dims + 1, &input_shape));
2087
2088 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2089 c->Merge(paddings_shape, c->Matrix(num_block_dims, 2), &paddings_shape));
2090
2091 DimensionHandle batch_size = c->Dim(input_shape, 0);
2092 std::vector<int64> block_shape_vec;
2093 if (block_shape_t) {
2094 block_shape_vec = GetFlatInt64(*block_shape_t);
2095 for (int64 dim = 0; dim < num_block_dims; ++dim) {
2096 const int64 block_shape_value = block_shape_vec[dim];
2097 if (block_shape_value < 1) {
2098 return errors::InvalidArgument("block_shape must be positive");
2099 }
2100 if (c->ValueKnown(batch_size)) {
2101 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2102 c->Multiply(batch_size, block_shape_value, &batch_size));
2103 } else {
2104 batch_size = c->UnknownDim();
2105 }
2106 }
2107 } else if (num_block_dims > 0) {
2108 batch_size = c->UnknownDim();
2109 }
2110
2111 std::vector<DimensionHandle> output_dims{batch_size};
2112 output_dims.resize(num_block_dims + 1, c->UnknownDim());
2113
2114 if (paddings_t) {
2115 const std::vector<int64> paddings_vec = GetFlatInt64(*paddings_t);
2116 for (int64 dim = 0; dim < num_block_dims; ++dim) {
2117 const int64 pad_start = paddings_vec[dim * 2],
2118 pad_end = paddings_vec[dim * 2 + 1];
2119 if (pad_start < 0 || pad_end < 0) {
2120 return errors::InvalidArgument("paddings cannot be negative");
2121 }
2122 if (block_shape_t) {
2123 DimensionHandle padded_size;
2124 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2125 c->Add(c->Dim(input_shape, dim + 1), pad_start, &padded_size));
2126 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Add(padded_size, pad_end, &padded_size));
2127 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Divide(padded_size, block_shape_vec[dim],
2128 /*evenly_divisible=*/true,
2129 &output_dims[dim + 1]));
2130 }
2131 }
2132 }
2133
2134 ShapeHandle remaining_input_shape;
2135 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2136 c->Subshape(input_shape, 1 + num_block_dims, &remaining_input_shape));
2137
2138 ShapeHandle result;
2139 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Concatenate(c->MakeShape(output_dims),
2140 remaining_input_shape, &result));
2141 c->set_output(0, result);
2142 return Status::OK();
2143}
2144
2145Status BatchToSpaceShapeHelper(InferenceContext* c, ShapeHandle input_shape,
2146 ShapeHandle block_shape_shape,
2147 const Tensor* block_shape_t,
2148 ShapeHandle crops_shape, const Tensor* crops_t) {
2149 if (c->Rank(block_shape_shape) != 1) {
2150 return errors::InvalidArgument("block_shape must have rank 1.");
2151 }
2152
2153 const DimensionHandle num_block_dims_handle = c->Dim(block_shape_shape, 0);
2154 if (!c->ValueKnown(num_block_dims_handle)) {
2155 return errors::InvalidArgument("block_shape must have known size.");
2156 }
2157
2158 const int64 num_block_dims = c->Value(num_block_dims_handle);
2159
2160 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2161 c->WithRankAtLeast(input_shape, num_block_dims + 1, &input_shape));
2162
2163 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2164 c->Merge(crops_shape, c->Matrix(num_block_dims, 2), &crops_shape));
2165
2166 DimensionHandle batch_size = c->Dim(input_shape, 0);
2167 std::vector<int64> block_shape_vec;
2168 if (block_shape_t) {
2169 block_shape_vec = GetFlatInt64(*block_shape_t);
2170 for (int64 dim = 0; dim < num_block_dims; ++dim) {
2171 const int64 block_shape_value = block_shape_vec[dim];
2172 if (block_shape_value < 1) {
2173 return errors::InvalidArgument("block_shape must be positive");
2174 }
2175 if (c->ValueKnown(batch_size)) {
2176 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Divide(batch_size, block_shape_value,
2177 /*evenly_divisible=*/true, &batch_size));
2178 } else {
2179 batch_size = c->UnknownDim();
2180 }
2181 }
2182 } else if (num_block_dims > 0) {
2183 batch_size = c->UnknownDim();
2184 }
2185
2186 std::vector<DimensionHandle> output_dims{batch_size};
2187 output_dims.resize(num_block_dims + 1, c->UnknownDim());
2188
2189 if (crops_t) {
2190 const std::vector<int64> crops_vec = GetFlatInt64(*crops_t);
2191 for (int64 dim = 0; dim < num_block_dims; ++dim) {
2192 const int64 crop_start = crops_vec[dim * 2],
2193 crop_end = crops_vec[dim * 2 + 1];
2194 if (crop_start < 0 || crop_end < 0) {
2195 return errors::InvalidArgument("crops cannot be negative");
2196 }
2197 if (block_shape_t) {
2198 DimensionHandle cropped_size;
2199 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Multiply(c->Dim(input_shape, dim + 1),
2200 block_shape_vec[dim], &cropped_size));
2201 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2202 c->Subtract(cropped_size, crop_start, &cropped_size));
2203 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2204 c->Subtract(cropped_size, crop_end, &output_dims[dim + 1]));
2205 }
2206 }
2207 }
2208
2209 ShapeHandle remaining_input_shape;
2210 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2211 c->Subshape(input_shape, 1 + num_block_dims, &remaining_input_shape));
2212
2213 ShapeHandle result;
2214 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Concatenate(c->MakeShape(output_dims),
2215 remaining_input_shape, &result));
2216 c->set_output(0, result);
2217 return Status::OK();
2218}

2303REGISTER_OP("SpaceToDepth")
2304 .Input("input: T")
2305 .Output("output: T")
2306 .Attr("T: type")
2307 .Attr("block_size: int >= 2")
2308 .Attr("data_format: {'NHWC', 'NCHW', 'NCHW_VECT_C'} = 'NHWC'")
2309 // TODO(pauldonnelly): Implement GPU kernels for NCHW_VECT_C.
2310 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
2311 string data_format_str;
2312 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->GetAttr("data_format", &data_format_str));
2313 TensorFormat data_format;
2314 FormatFromString(data_format_str, &data_format);
2315
2316 constexpr int num_spatial_dims = 2;
2317 const int dims =
2318 GetTensorDimsFromSpatialDims(num_spatial_dims, data_format);
2319 ShapeHandle input;
2320 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(c->input(0), dims, &input));
2321
2322 int32 block_size;
2323 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->GetAttr("block_size", &block_size));
2324
2325 DimensionHandle batch_size =
2326 c->Dim(input, GetTensorDimIndex<num_spatial_dims>(data_format, 'N'));
2327 DimensionHandle input_height =
2328 c->Dim(input, GetTensorDimIndex<num_spatial_dims>(data_format, 'H'));
2329 DimensionHandle input_width =
2330 c->Dim(input, GetTensorDimIndex<num_spatial_dims>(data_format, 'W'));
2331 DimensionHandle input_depth =
2332 c->Dim(input, GetTensorDimIndex<num_spatial_dims>(data_format, 'C'));
2333
2334 DimensionHandle output_height;
2335 DimensionHandle output_width;
2336 DimensionHandle output_depth;
2337 // Will return an error if input height or width are not evenly divisible.
2338 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Divide(input_height, block_size,
2339 true /* evenly_divisible */,
2340 &output_height));
2341 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Divide(input_width, block_size,
2342 true /* evenly_divisible */, &output_width));
2343
2344 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2345 c->Multiply(input_depth, block_size * block_size, &output_depth));
2346
2347 ShapeHandle output_shape;
2348 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(MakeShapeFromFormat(data_format, batch_size,
2349 {output_height, output_width},
2350 output_depth, &output_shape, c));
2351
2352 c->set_output(0, output_shape);
2353 return Status::OK();

2410REGISTER_OP("ExtractImagePatches")
2411 .Input("images: T")
2412 .Output("patches: T")
2413 .Attr("ksizes: list(int) >= 4")
2414 .Attr("strides: list(int) >= 4")
2415 .Attr("rates: list(int) >= 4")
2416 .Attr("T: realnumbertype")
2417 .Attr(GetPaddingAttrString())
2418 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
2419 ShapeHandle input_shape;
2420 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRank(c->input(0), 4, &input_shape));
2421
2422 std::vector<int32> ksizes;
2423 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->GetAttr("ksizes", &ksizes));
2424 if (ksizes.size() != 4) {
2425 return errors::InvalidArgument(
2426 "ExtractImagePatches requires the ksizes attribute to contain 4 "
2427 "values, but got: ",
2428 ksizes.size());
2429 }
2430
2431 std::vector<int32> strides;
2432 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->GetAttr("strides", &strides));
2433 if (strides.size() != 4) {
2434 return errors::InvalidArgument(
2435 "ExtractImagePatches requires the stride attribute to contain 4 "
2436 "values, but got: ",
2437 strides.size());
2438 }
2439
2440 std::vector<int32> rates;
2441 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->GetAttr("rates", &rates));
2442 if (rates.size() != 4) {
2443 return errors::InvalidArgument(
2444 "ExtractImagePatches requires the rates attribute to contain 4 "
2445 "values, but got: ",
2446 rates.size());
2447 }
2448
2449 int32 ksize_rows = ksizes[1];
2450 int32 ksize_cols = ksizes[2];
2451
2452 int32 stride_rows = strides[1];
2453 int32 stride_cols = strides[2];
2454
2455 int32 rate_rows = rates[1];
2456 int32 rate_cols = rates[2];
2457
2458 int32 ksize_rows_eff = ksize_rows + (ksize_rows - 1) * (rate_rows - 1);
2459 int32 ksize_cols_eff = ksize_cols + (ksize_cols - 1) * (rate_cols - 1);
2460
2461 DimensionHandle batch_size_dim = c->Dim(input_shape, 0);
2462 DimensionHandle in_rows_dim = c->Dim(input_shape, 1);
2463 DimensionHandle in_cols_dim = c->Dim(input_shape, 2);
2464 DimensionHandle output_depth_dim;
2465 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Multiply(
2466 c->Dim(input_shape, 3), ksize_rows * ksize_cols, &output_depth_dim));
2467
2468 if (!c->ValueKnown(in_rows_dim) || !c->ValueKnown(in_cols_dim)) {
2469 ShapeHandle output_shape =
2470 c->MakeShape({batch_size_dim, InferenceContext::kUnknownDim,
2471 InferenceContext::kUnknownDim, output_depth_dim});
2472 c->set_output(0, output_shape);
2473 return Status::OK();
2474 }
2475 auto in_rows = c->Value(in_rows_dim);
2476 auto in_cols = c->Value(in_cols_dim);
2477
2478 Padding padding;
2479 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->GetAttr("padding", &padding));
2480
2481 int64 output_rows, output_cols;
2482 int64 padding_before, padding_after;
2483 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(GetWindowedOutputSizeVerbose(
2484 in_rows, ksize_rows_eff, stride_rows, padding, &output_rows,
2485 &padding_before, &padding_after));
2486 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(GetWindowedOutputSizeVerbose(
2487 in_cols, ksize_cols_eff, stride_cols, padding, &output_cols,
2488 &padding_before, &padding_after));
2489 ShapeHandle output_shape = c->MakeShape(
2490 {batch_size_dim, output_rows, output_cols, output_depth_dim});
2491 c->set_output(0, output_shape);
2492 return Status::OK();
2493 });
2494

2497REGISTER_OP("Bitcast")
2498 .Input("input: T")
2499 .Output("output: type")
2500 // All supported dtypes are listed here to include qint16 and quint16.
2501 .Attr(
2502 "T: {bfloat16, half, float, double, int64, int32, uint8, uint16, int8, "
2503 "int16, complex64, complex128, qint8, quint8, qint16, quint16, qint32}")
2504 .Attr(
2505 "type: {bfloat16, half, float, double, int64, int32, uint8, uint16, "
2506 "int8, int16, complex64, complex128, qint8, quint8, qint16, quint16, "
2507 "qint32}")
2508 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
2509 ShapeHandle input = c->input(0);
2510 if (!c->RankKnown(input)) {
2511 // Input shape unknown.
2512 return shape_inference::UnknownShape(c);
2513 }
2514
2515 // Find the size of the input and output data types.
2516 DataType input_type;
2517 DataType output_type;
2518 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->GetAttr("T", &input_type));
2519 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->GetAttr("type", &output_type));
2520 const int input_type_size = DataTypeSize(input_type);
2521 const int output_type_size = DataTypeSize(output_type);
2522
2523 if (input_type_size == 0 || output_type_size == 0) {
2524 return errors::InvalidArgument("Cannot bitcast types ",
2525 DataTypeString(input_type), " to ",
2526 DataTypeString(output_type),
2527 " because "
2528 "one of the type sizes is zero.");
2529 }
2530
2531 ShapeHandle new_shape;
2532 if (input_type_size == output_type_size) {
2533 // No change in size.
2534 new_shape = input;
2535 } else if (input_type_size < output_type_size) {
2536 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRankAtLeast(input, 1, &new_shape));
2537
2538 int64 divisor_val = output_type_size / input_type_size;
2539 DimensionHandle last_dim = c->Dim(new_shape, -1);
2540 if (!c->ValueKnown(last_dim) || c->Value(last_dim) == divisor_val) {
2541 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Subshape(new_shape, 0, -1, &new_shape));
2542 } else {
2543 return errors::InvalidArgument("Cannot bitcast due to shape. ",
2544 c->Value(last_dim), " does not match ",
2545 divisor_val);
2546 }
2547 } else {
2548 // Input type size is larger than output type size.
2549 int64 divisor_val = input_type_size / output_type_size;
2550 ShapeHandle extension = c->Vector(divisor_val);
2551 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Concatenate(input, extension, &new_shape));
2552 }
2553
2554 c->set_output(0, new_shape);
2555 return Status::OK();
2556 });
2557
2558REGISTER_OP("OneHot")
2559 .Input("indices: TI")
2560 .Input("depth: int32")
2561 .Input("on_value: T")
2562 .Input("off_value: T")
2563 .Attr("axis: int = -1")
2564 .Output("output: T")
2565 .Attr("T: type")
2566 .Attr("TI: {uint8, int32, int64} = DT_INT64")
2567 .SetShapeFn([](InferenceContext* c) {
2568 int32 axis;
2569 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->GetAttr("axis", &axis));
2570 if (axis < -1) return errors::InvalidArgument("axis must be >= -1");
2571
2572 DimensionHandle depth;
2573 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->MakeDimForScalarInput(1, &depth));
2574
2575 ShapeHandle indices = c->input(0);
2576 if (!c->RankKnown(indices)) return shape_inference::UnknownShape(c);
2577
2578 int32 new_rank = c->Rank(indices) + 1;
2579 // We need to add new_rank to axis in the case the axis is -1 because
2580 // C++ returns negative values from % if the dividend is negative.
2581 int32 depth_index = (axis + new_rank) % new_rank;
2582 // Out shape is indices[0:depth_index] + [depth] + indices[depth_index:].
2583 ShapeHandle front;
2584 ShapeHandle back;
2585 ShapeHandle out;
2586 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Subshape(indices, 0, depth_index, &front));
2587 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Subshape(indices, depth_index, &back));
2588 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Concatenate(front, c->Vector(depth), &front));
2589 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Concatenate(front, back, &out));
2590 c->set_output(0, out);
2591 return Status::OK();
2592 });

2752Status ScatterNdShape(InferenceContext* c) {
2753 ShapeHandle indices_shape;
2754 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRankAtLeast(c->input(0), 1, &indices_shape));
2755 ShapeHandle updates_shape;
2756 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->WithRankAtLeast(c->input(1), 1, &updates_shape));
2757 ShapeHandle output_shape;
2758 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->MakeShapeFromShapeTensor(2, &output_shape));
2759
2760 if (c->Value(c->NumElements(output_shape)) == 0 &&
2761 (c->Value(c->NumElements(indices_shape)) > 0 ||
2762 c->Value(c->NumElements(updates_shape)) > 0)) {
2763 return errors::InvalidArgument(
2764 "Indices and updates specified for empty output shape");
2765 }
2766
2767 if (c->RankKnown(indices_shape) && c->RankKnown(updates_shape)) {
2768 const int64 outer_dims = c->Rank(indices_shape) - 1;
2769 const DimensionHandle ixdim = c->Dim(indices_shape, -1);
2770
2771 // We can only do more validation if the last dimension of indices
2772 // is a known value.
2773 if (c->ValueKnown(ixdim)) {
2774 int64 ix = c->Value(ixdim);
2775 ShapeHandle unused;
2776 ShapeHandle prefix_indices;
2777 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2778 c->Subshape(indices_shape, 0, outer_dims, &prefix_indices));
2779 ShapeHandle prefix_updates;
2780 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2781 c->Subshape(updates_shape, 0, outer_dims, &prefix_updates));
2782
2783 Status s = c->Merge(prefix_indices, prefix_updates, &unused);
2784 if (!s.ok()) {
2785 return errors::InvalidArgument(
2786 "The outer ", outer_dims,
2787 " dimensions of indices.shape=", c->DebugString(indices_shape),
2788 " must match the outer ", outer_dims,
2789 " dimensions of updates.shape=", c->DebugString(updates_shape),
2790 ": ", s.error_message());
2791 }
2792
2793 ShapeHandle suffix_output;
2794 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(c->Subshape(output_shape, ix, &suffix_output));
2795 ShapeHandle suffix_updates;
2796 TF_RETURN_IF_ERROR(
2797 c->Subshape(updates_shape, outer_dims, &suffix_updates));
2798 s = c->Merge(suffix_output, suffix_updates, &unused);
2799 if (!s.ok()) {
2800 return errors::InvalidArgument(
2801 "The inner ", c->Rank(output_shape) - ix,
2802 " dimensions of output.shape=", c->DebugString(output_shape),
2803 " must match the inner ", c->Rank(updates_shape) - outer_dims,
2804 " dimensions of updates.shape=", c->DebugString(updates_shape),
2805 ": ", s.error_message());
2806 }
2807 }
2808 }
2809
2810 c->set_output(0, output_shape);
2811 return Status::OK();
2812}
